{"id": 262, "date": "1988-02-29T11:30:44", "date_gmt": "1988-02-29T19:30:44", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=262"}, "modified": "2026-02-08T05:30:29", "modified_gmt": "2026-02-08T13:30:29", "slug": "meeting-across-the-river-emmylou-harris-bruce-springsteen-patti-scialfa", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1988/02/29/meeting-across-the-river-emmylou-harris-bruce-springsteen-patti-scialfa/", "title": {"rendered": "Tragedy"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>From Emmylou Harris&#8217; Grammy-winning album\u00a0<em>Red Dirt Girl</em> comes the graceful &#8220;Tragedy,&#8221; with restrained, haunting background vocals by Bruce and Patti.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/jf7BSf5ezUY?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>We&#8217;ve featured Emmylou on the blog several times over the years, always spotlighting her beautiful covers of Bruce&#8217;s music. Bruce&#8217;s music has been an influence on Emmylou&#8217;s studio work for decades, however. In fact, her 1985 album <em>The Ballad of Sally Rose</em> was directly inspired by\u00a0<em>Nebraska.</em></p>\n<p>So it&#8217;s surprising that this turn-of-the-century track so deep into their careers marks their first studio collaboration, but the wait resulted in a beautiful song.</p>\n<p><strong>Tragedy<br />\nRecorded:</strong> March 20, 2000<br />\n<strong>Released:</strong>\u00a0<em>Red Dirt Girl</em> (2000)<br />\n<strong>Never performed</strong></p>\n<p>\u00a9 January 17, 2018</p>\n"